{
  "analysis": "Found the password pattern in the .dat file. The strings output shows 'PASSWORD=8XDP5Q2RT9Z' and then 'K7VB3BV4WW54' on the next line, indicating the password is split across a newline in the file. The full password is 23 characters, starts with 8XD, ends with W54, and matches all criteria. Need to extract the exact password string and write it to the recovery file.",
  "plan": "1. Use grep with binary flag to extract the password pattern across newline if possible. 2. Alternatively, use xxd or od to verify the exact string. 3. Write the password to /app/recovered_passwords.txt.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -a -o 'PASSWORD=[A-Z0-9]*' /app/varsea/disks/sub1/subA/subAlpha/ae3f4c.dat 2>/dev/null\n",
      "duration": 0.1
